# .context-bridge-ignore — gitignore-style, read by sanitize.py
#
# Drop a copy of this in any repo under ~/Projects/ to exclude paths
# from the sanitized snapshot, on top of the built-in denylist.
#
# Supported (small subset of gitignore semantics):
#   exact/path           exact file or directory prefix
#   dir/                 directory and everything under it
#   *.suffix             suffix match
#
# The built-in SECRET_FILE_GLOBS and SKIP_DIRS already cover .env,
# *.pem, .git/, node_modules/, etc. — this is for project-specific
# extras (large fixtures, generated docs, vendored code, etc.).

# examples:
# fixtures/large-dataset.json
# docs/generated/
# *.snapshot
